==English==
===Etymology===
*[[pre-]] + [[append|(ap)pend]], by analogy with '''append'''

*Although it sounds correct, prepend is not an English word. It was created to sound like the opposite of "append," which means to add to the end. The correct English word is "prefix;" for example, "the header is prefixed to the packet." 

===Transitive verb===
#{{computing}} To [[append]] (something) to the front of an [[expression]].

